Rexfelix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:17:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> When you create a dark elf, there's something in the text at the beginning that says &quot;Fill the Ocean of Tears with fair elven corpses&quot;, or some such. Trolls are perverse monsters who think it is fun to rip something apart limb from limb and watch the innards fall out. Ogres are either the &quot;epitome of the strength of evil&quot; or huge creatures who eat everything they see. Iksar are reptilian bigots who have spent their entire history killing and enslaving anyone and everyone they could get their claws on.<br>
<br>
An &quot;uneasy alliance&quot; (as I see it, and I'm certainly not an expert) would be an alliance between a human guild and a high elven guild to do somethingorother. They don't necessarily trust one another, but they don't hate each other, so they band together reluctantly and do what needs to be done (remember how the people of Gondor distrusted the elves in Lothlorien?)<br>
<br>
But an alliance between evil and good in EQ...that'd be like if someone killed my family, and then I &quot;grouped&quot; with the murderer to do something. Or like if the elves in Lorien decided to team up with the orcs to do something. It just wouldn't happen.The evils want to kill or manipulate the goods, and the goods understand they could be betrayed at any time, and killed and tortured. Can you picture an RL priest &quot;grouping&quot; with a blasphemous homicidal maniac for any reason? <br>
<br>
Okay, so I'm not saying that this could never ever happen. But some seriously intense and drawn-out RP would have to happen before it got to the point where it was really believable. And something tells me when it comes down to it, when there's a semi-high level good guild and a semi-high level evil guild, and high_level_mob_01 is ripe for the picking...RP will be gently pushed to the side. And I don't think that's a good thing for the server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubormwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:42:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> /sigh<br>
