<br>
To say that good and evil, troll and woodelf CANNOT mix under any circumstances and if they do it's a cop out is pretty weak.  Fantasy literature is full (as per my previous examples) of these types of alliances.  It is up to the people, however, to make the whole thing work out.  <br>
<br>
Think about how boring the Dragonlance series would have been if Tanis said &quot;Raistlin, you evil bastard...I cannot group with you and kill mobs...&quot; and then he proceeded to kill him or kick him out of the group.  It's the conflict of the intermingling of opposing types that makes that stuff interesting. <br>
<br>
For those so-called roleplayers who are drawing some imaginary line in the sand, step up to the plate and prove you are a roleplayer by using your imagination and make the whole thing interesting rather than a semantic arguement over &quot;I am good elf, I cannot help an evil ogre with anything.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rexfelix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 5:22:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> Is the only way for a Roleplayer to get to the Highend game is to RP in one defined way?<br>
